WEBVTT

00:08.258 --> 00:09.676
<i>Previously on </i>Riverdale:

00:09.759 --> 00:12.387
-It's yours, Archie.

00:12.470 --> 00:16.099
This is what guys like Chuck think
about women. We're objects.

00:16.182 --> 00:18.059
Cheryl was obsessed with you.

00:18.143 --> 00:21.521
-I was afraid she might hurt you.
-Cheryl threatened me.

00:21.604 --> 00:23.189
Know about Southside High closing?

00:23.273 --> 00:25.984
You acted like you didn't know.
I can't trust you, V.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.989
Chic, you should leave this house.

00:31.072 --> 00:35.827
I hurried back for <i>Carrie: The Musical</i>.
And this school's gonna burn.

00:38.788 --> 00:42.792
-Jughead, thank you for meeting me.
-I know what you're gonna ask.

00:42.876 --> 00:47.046
I'm making a documentary following
our production of <i>Carrie</i>.

00:47.714 --> 00:51.342
We're going period, '70s glamour,
like the Sissy Spacek movie.

00:51.426 --> 00:53.261
I want you to be our videographer.

00:55.805 --> 00:56.639
I'm in.

01:14.449 --> 01:19.370
♪  <i>Every day I just pray</i>
<i>Every move I make is right ♪</i>

01:19.454 --> 01:22.165
<i>♪ Where I go, who I know ♪</i>

01:22.248 --> 01:27.003
<i>♪ Will I be alone on Saturday night? ♪</i>

01:27.086 --> 01:32.050
<i>♪ I don't worry if I blow my SATs ♪</i>

01:32.133 --> 01:37.222
<i>♪ I worry what can I possibly do ♪</i>

01:37.305 --> 01:38.848
<i>♪ To squeeze in</i>
<i>Pow ♪</i>

01:38.932 --> 01:40.183
<i>♪ Why not now? ♪</i>

01:40.266 --> 01:44.229
<i>♪ When will I belong?</i>
<i>Look where I am, damn ♪</i>

01:44.312 --> 01:47.607
<i>♪ My whole life feels wrong ♪</i>

01:47.690 --> 01:50.610
<i>♪ What if I do snap?</i>
<i>Holy crap ♪</i>

01:50.693 --> 01:53.738
<i>♪ I'd crawl out of my skin</i>
<i>And so would you ♪</i>

01:53.822 --> 01:58.868
<i>♪ 'Cause life just doesn't begin</i>
<i>Until you're in ♪</i>

01:58.952 --> 02:03.081
Maybe Andrews Construction
could help build the sets for the musical.

02:03.164 --> 02:06.000
I got the lumber, the tools,
I'm in between gigs.

02:06.084 --> 02:07.710
-Absolutely.

02:07.794 --> 02:11.339
I'm thrilled you're getting back
into music.

02:11.422 --> 02:13.842
Been a while since
we spent time together.

02:13.925 --> 02:16.177
-Awesome.
-Great. I'll give you a ride.

02:16.386 --> 02:19.681
Uh... I'm good.
I'm gonna take my bike, thanks.

02:23.768 --> 02:28.857
♪  <i>God, it's rough staying tough</i>
<i>Wondering what the world will say ♪</i>

02:28.940 --> 02:31.401
<i>♪ Make a plan</i>
<i>Be a man ♪</i>

02:31.484 --> 02:35.905
<i>♪ All this fricking crap</i>
<i>Just gets in the way ♪</i>

02:35.989 --> 02:41.202
<i>♪ I go crazy</i>
<i>Nobody cares what it does to me ♪</i>

02:41.286 --> 02:46.249
<i>♪ And it's crazy</i>
<i>I would go out of my mind ♪</i>

02:46.332 --> 02:48.918
<i> Am I ♪</i>
<i>-♪ To be in it, in is it ♪</i>

02:49.002 --> 02:51.546
<i>♪ What comes close to that? ♪</i>

02:51.629 --> 02:56.718
<i>♪ Until you've been in</i>
<i>You ain't where it's at ♪</i>

02:56.801 --> 02:59.137
<i>♪ 'Cause when you're out</i>
<i>Well, life is hell ♪</i>

02:59.220 --> 03:01.931
<i>♪ You can never win ♪</i>

03:02.015 --> 03:06.728
<i>♪ There's no doubt</i>
<i>That life just doesn't begin ♪</i>

03:07.312 --> 03:09.939
<i>♪ Doesn't begin ♪</i>

03:10.023 --> 03:13.276
<i>♪ Doesn't begin ♪</i>

03:15.194 --> 03:19.949
<i>♪ Until you're in ♪</i>

03:23.536 --> 03:25.580
Welcome to <i>Carrie: The Musical</i>.

03:29.167 --> 03:30.126
Hey, Fangs.

03:30.710 --> 03:32.462
Okay, next. Introductions.

03:33.004 --> 03:36.841
I'm, uh, Archie.
I'm playing Tommy Ross, the boy next door. I'm Betty.
I play Sue Snell, the good girl.

03:42.096 --> 03:45.516
Veronica Lodge,
playing mean girl Chris Hargensen.

03:46.768 --> 03:50.438
I'm Cheryl Blossom,
playing the iconic role of Carrie White.

03:54.067 --> 03:55.318
Tone deaf.

03:56.903 --> 03:59.822
-I am.

04:00.823 --> 04:03.201
-Mom.

04:03.284 --> 04:04.410
Settle down.

04:05.245 --> 04:06.996
-It's untraditional.

04:07.080 --> 04:10.458
But nothing's more amateur
than age-inappropriate casting.

04:10.541 --> 04:15.004
I'm looking forward to getting to know
this woman, get under her skin.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.507
And spend some time
with my daughter Elizabeth.

04:19.717 --> 04:24.055
Sorry. I thought rehearsal
was in the Music Room.

04:24.138 --> 04:27.308
No problem. All are welcome here.

04:28.142 --> 04:31.145
<i>So,</i>  <i>Chuck Clayton...</i>

04:31.229 --> 04:34.023
Why did you say yes
to being in the musical?

04:35.024 --> 04:37.360
I'm trying to reform my image.

04:37.568 --> 04:41.531
And, yeah, maybe it's counter-intuitive
to be playing the villain,

04:42.115 --> 04:45.618
but somebody's gotta do it.
And I wanna do it right.

04:46.369 --> 04:51.082
You know, show up, put in the work,
be a member of the team.

04:53.584 --> 04:58.423
And, who knows, maybe then people will
start to change their minds about me.

04:59.132 --> 05:02.468
Kind of weird, huh? The two of us
playing boyfriend and girlfriend.

05:02.552 --> 05:05.305
Easy there, Arch.
Big Brother's watching.

05:06.639 --> 05:09.934
No, I mean, things are strained
with the four of us,

05:10.018 --> 05:13.855
but we're here for Kevin, to do this play.
Let's make it painless.

05:13.938 --> 05:18.067
Archie, Veronica lied to all of us,
you included.

05:18.651 --> 05:21.612
Conspiring with her parents
against the school?

05:21.696 --> 05:25.158
It's fine that you're doing
what Tommy Ross would do,

05:25.241 --> 05:28.286
which is stand by her.
But from where I'm standing?

05:28.369 --> 05:32.290
Veronica's as much of a privileged,
selfish, spiteful mean girl

05:32.373 --> 05:34.334
as the part she's playing.

05:36.127 --> 05:37.670
Okay, Act One, Scene One.

05:38.379 --> 05:41.966
Actually... before we begin...

05:43.885 --> 05:47.221
I've heard whisperings
that some of you ensemble-vultures

05:47.305 --> 05:49.974
don't think I'm fit to play, or sing...

05:50.058 --> 05:51.893
-No.
-the role of Carrie White.

05:53.728 --> 05:56.647
So, to settle this
once and for all... Maestro?

05:56.731 --> 05:57.690
Okay, uh, Cheryl--

05:57.774 --> 06:02.236
<i>♪ </i> <i>That's not my name ♪</i>

06:02.320 --> 06:03.571
Uh, Cheryl.

06:03.654 --> 06:07.241
<i>♪ I'd hear that word</i>
<i>Sounding so sweet ♪</i>

06:07.325 --> 06:12.330
<i>♪ Thousands of voices forever repeating</i>
<i>Carrie ♪</i>

06:12.413 --> 06:15.875
<i>♪ Carrie</i>
<i>Carrie ♪</i>

06:16.459 --> 06:20.046
<i>♪ I am the sound of distant thunder ♪</i>

06:20.129 --> 06:21.672
<i>♪ That color, a flame ♪</i>

06:22.256 --> 06:24.801
<i>♪ I'm Carrie ♪</i>

06:24.884 --> 06:30.473
<i>♪ I am a song of endless wonder</i>
<i>That no one will claim ♪</i>

06:30.556 --> 06:36.938
<i>♪ But someday</i>
<i>Oh, my, someday ♪</i>

06:37.021 --> 06:43.486
<i>♪ Someone will know my name ♪</i>

06:53.621 --> 06:57.500
Wow. I think I speak for everyone
when I say that was undeniable.

07:12.473 --> 07:14.684
I have a dark confession to make.

07:15.476 --> 07:17.854
After Cheryl's brush with death,

07:17.937 --> 07:22.483
I found a letter in my locker
from someone alleging to be--

07:22.567 --> 07:25.111
And I can't believe
I'm about to say this.

07:25.611 --> 07:27.280
--the Black Hood.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.995
It's a prank. Look at it.

07:35.621 --> 07:38.916
Why would the Black Hood,
who was shot dead by my dad,

07:39.000 --> 07:41.752
be demanding
that the role of Carrie be recast?

07:41.836 --> 07:45.131
It does seem
pretty small potatoes for the Black Hood.

07:45.214 --> 07:49.218
Yeah. Still, Jug,
you can't tell anyone about this.

07:50.178 --> 07:53.723
As official documentarian,
you're sworn to secrecy.

07:54.307 --> 07:58.644
Also, the show, as they say, must go on.

07:59.520 --> 08:03.983
♪  <i>Tommy, lately</i>
<i>I've just not been feeling right ♪</i>

08:05.109 --> 08:11.240
<i>♪ I'm so ashamed of how</i>
<i>We've all been treating Carrie White ♪</i>

08:12.700 --> 08:17.371
<i>♪ Now, I realize</i>
<i>This is hardly your concern ♪</i>

08:18.456 --> 08:24.086
<i>♪ I hate to drag you into this</i>
<i>But I've got nowhere else to turn ♪</i>

08:24.754 --> 08:26.380
<i>♪ Do me a favor ♪</i>

08:26.464 --> 08:29.884
<i>♪ There's something that Carrie White</i>
<i>Will just have to learn ♪</i>

08:29.967 --> 08:33.137
<i>♪ If she plays with fire</i>
<i>She's gonna get burned ♪</i>

08:33.221 --> 08:36.015
<i>♪ I want her to pay up</i>
<i>For all that she cost me ♪</i>

08:36.098 --> 08:39.560
<i>♪ And make her good and sorry</i>
<i>That she ever crossed me ♪</i>

08:39.644 --> 08:42.063
<i>-♪ You gotta help me ♪</i>
<i>-♪ If you help me ♪</i>

08:42.146 --> 08:44.941
<i>♪ I could even up this debt ♪</i>

08:45.024 --> 08:51.072
<i>♪ And we could both give Carrie White</i>
<i>A night she won't forget ♪</i>

08:51.155 --> 08:52.865
<i>♪ Do me a favor ♪</i>

08:54.575 --> 08:59.747
<i>♪ Think of Carrie</i>
<i>I've said everything I could ♪</i>

08:59.956 --> 09:06.462
<i>♪ But one small act of kindness</i>
<i>Might change Carrie's life for good ♪</i>

09:06.546 --> 09:09.090
-Fine.
<i>-♪ Come on, come on ♪</i>

09:09.674 --> 09:12.677
<i>♪ Okay, okay, okay ♪</i>

09:13.970 --> 09:17.390
<i>♪ There's something that Carrie White</i>
<i>Will just have to learn ♪</i>

09:17.473 --> 09:20.101
<i>♪ If she plays with fire</i>
<i>She's gonna get burned ♪</i>

09:20.184 --> 09:23.646
<i>♪ I'm begging, I'm pleading</i>
<i>I'm down on my knees ♪</i>

09:23.729 --> 09:28.943
<i>♪ If you really love me</i>
<i>Well, then, baby, baby, please ♪</i>

09:29.026 --> 09:31.070
<i>♪ Do me a favor ♪</i>

09:35.866 --> 09:39.203
Ronnie, I need to ask you something.

09:40.663 --> 09:45.293
What? You want us to take that sexy new
Firebird of yours to Lovers' Lane?

09:50.715 --> 09:53.884
I was gonna ask if I could keep it
at the Pembrooke.

09:53.968 --> 09:54.802
Why?

09:56.137 --> 09:58.681
I haven't told my dad about the Firebird.

09:59.098 --> 10:01.017
And our dads are literal rivals.

10:01.100 --> 10:03.811
If my dad finds out
yours gave me this gift,

10:03.894 --> 10:05.855
it'll trigger World War III.

10:06.188 --> 10:09.358
Fine. Our garage is your garage. About the election,
you really think Fred has a shot?

10:16.616 --> 10:20.953
In our favor, he's essentially running
on a platform of family values

10:21.037 --> 10:24.582
with none of his family by his side.
Mary's gone, thank God.

10:25.041 --> 10:29.545
And, well, Archie and Fred,
they've never been so distant, have they?

10:31.631 --> 10:33.674
We just need to keep it that way.

10:36.761 --> 10:38.512
No way is this legit.

10:38.596 --> 10:42.099
It's a legit threat,
but it's not from the real Black Hood.

10:42.183 --> 10:45.102
No. This is a classic
<i>Phantom of the Opera</i> tactic.

10:45.519 --> 10:47.521
Mystery man sends menacing note

10:47.605 --> 10:51.651
demanding a certain diva soprano
gets recast or else...

10:51.734 --> 10:55.029
Who's to say this letter came
from a mystery man at all?

10:55.112 --> 10:56.864
That's a good point.

10:59.033 --> 11:01.285
Hey, Ethel, what looks good?

11:01.369 --> 11:03.496
Someone picked out all the M&amp;M's
from the trail mix.

11:03.579 --> 11:07.208
Ugh. That's terrible.
It was probably Cheryl.

11:07.291 --> 11:10.002
She's always taking things
that she shouldn't,

11:10.086 --> 11:12.380
like the role of Carrie from you.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.466
That's nice of you to say, Betty.

11:16.092 --> 11:20.763
For Kevin to have cast Cheryl as Carrie
without even letting you audition...

11:23.849 --> 11:26.268
Would you say you feel angry?

11:26.852 --> 11:28.854
I mean, I was born to play Carrie.

11:30.106 --> 11:33.859
So, not to be given a shot at it,
yeah, it makes me angry.

11:40.658 --> 11:44.495
-No. Oh, no, no.

11:45.788 --> 11:47.748
No, he's shooting B-roll.

11:47.832 --> 11:50.918
I have no idea what you're trying
to get me to admit,

11:51.001 --> 11:55.506
but I am not a violent person.
And I would never do anything

11:55.589 --> 11:59.176
to threaten or harm anybody
for my own benefit, ever.

12:05.558 --> 12:09.019
[Dan Auerbach's "Up on a Mountain of Love"
playing on speakers]

12:19.113 --> 12:20.614
Just finished rehearsal.

12:21.157 --> 12:24.368
I'm in the high school musical.
Can you believe it?

12:28.664 --> 12:32.501
Maybe you'll come by, check it out?

12:34.128 --> 12:36.297
I'm working, Alice. Sorry.

12:39.467 --> 12:42.845
Wow, really

12:45.639 --> 12:50.060
You know what's funny? I was afraid
our kids would make the mistakes we did.

12:50.144 --> 12:53.314
Turns out we're the ones making them
all over again.

12:54.773 --> 13:00.571
<i>♪ When you're up on a mountain of</i>
<i>On a mountain of love ♪</i>

13:01.363 --> 13:05.951
In this scene, teacher Mrs. Gardener
is being a friend when our girl has none,

13:06.035 --> 13:08.829
-out of kindness.
-I'll fake it as best I can.

13:13.334 --> 13:17.671
♪ <i> So many years</i>
<i>You faced the world alone ♪</i>

13:17.755 --> 13:22.468
<i>♪ Frightened that life might pass you by ♪</i>

13:24.136 --> 13:28.182
<i>♪ Then he appears</i>
<i>Someone who smiles at you ♪</i>

13:28.516 --> 13:32.686
<i>♪ This is no time to question why ♪</i>

13:32.770 --> 13:34.104
Stop, stop. Stop!

13:34.855 --> 13:37.358
I'm the only one that's allowed to stop.

13:37.441 --> 13:42.321
I can't do this, have you hating me
while we're singing about friendship.

13:43.364 --> 13:46.492
I know everything I did
was legit crazy, Josie.

13:47.076 --> 13:52.706
But I was wrestling
with some dark, Carrie White-like demons.

13:53.332 --> 13:56.669
I'm so, so sorry.

13:57.920 --> 14:01.298
So, please, please forgive me.

14:05.928 --> 14:09.848
<i>♪ </i> <i>That's how it starts ♪</i>

14:09.932 --> 14:13.269
<i>♪ Two unsuspecting hearts ♪</i>

14:13.352 --> 14:19.692
<i>♪ In a world where nothing's sure</i>
<i>And nothing's ever guaranteed ♪</i>

14:19.775 --> 14:24.113
<i>-♪ Nothing's guaranteed ♪</i>
<i>-♪ You should trust the way you feel ♪</i>

14:24.196 --> 14:29.285
<i>-♪ Trust the way you feel ♪</i>
<i>-♪ That's the only thing that's real ♪</i>

14:29.368 --> 14:34.331
<i>♪ It's like magic how your spirit soars ♪</i>

14:34.415 --> 14:38.043
<i>♪ Once you feel his hand in yours ♪</i>

14:38.127 --> 14:42.590
<i>-♪ That's how it, that's how it starts ♪</i>
<i>-♪ That's how it ♪</i>

14:42.673 --> 14:49.680
<i>-♪ Two unsuspecting hearts ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Two unsuspecting hearts ♪</i>

14:59.273 --> 15:03.861
Veronica, <i>mija</i>. I noticed the Firebird
parked in the Pembrooke garage.

15:03.944 --> 15:05.321
Is there a problem?

15:05.404 --> 15:09.950
No, Daddy. Archie is parking it here
until he tells Fred you gave it to him.

15:10.034 --> 15:12.786
He's worried
he's gonna bruise his dad's ego.

15:12.870 --> 15:14.455
-That makes sense.
-Yep.

15:19.168 --> 15:20.628
Cheers, <i>mi alma</i>.

15:21.754 --> 15:25.841
In keeping with this week's theme,
I've just had a wicked idea.

15:39.271 --> 15:41.690
<i>♪ </i> <i>Guess what</i>
<i>Ever since the world began ♪</i>

15:41.774 --> 15:42.900
<i>♪ Same plot ♪</i>

15:42.983 --> 15:46.028
<i>♪ Everyone's been dumping</i>
<i>On their fellow man ♪</i>

15:46.111 --> 15:49.448
<i>♪ Pounding people they feel better than ♪</i>

15:49.531 --> 15:53.869
<i>♪ I hope you're taking notes</i>
<i>'Cause you feel everyone deserves a shot ♪</i>

15:54.203 --> 15:58.040
<i>♪ Get real, some of us have got it, girl</i>
<i>And some got squat ♪</i>

15:58.123 --> 16:01.502
<i>♪ That's the truth, oh, honey</i>
<i>Like it or not ♪</i>

16:01.585 --> 16:03.087
<i>♪ I hate to break it to you ♪</i>

16:03.170 --> 16:08.509
<i>♪ My daddy taught me</i>
<i>You get nowhere being nice ♪</i>

16:09.051 --> 16:12.680
<i>♪ So, now I'm sharing his advice ♪</i>

16:13.514 --> 16:18.143
<i>♪ The world according to Chris is</i>
<i>Better to strike than get struck ♪</i>

16:19.186 --> 16:21.230
<i>♪ Better to screw than get screwed ♪</i>

16:21.313 --> 16:25.275
<i>♪ You'd probably think it's bizarre ♪</i>

16:25.359 --> 16:27.277
<i>♪ And that's the way things are ♪</i>

16:28.278 --> 16:32.741
<i>♪ My daddy taught me who's on top</i>
<i>And who's below ♪</i>

16:34.368 --> 16:37.830
<i>♪ And now it's time I let you know ♪</i>

16:38.831 --> 16:43.794
<i>♪ The world according to Chris is</i>
<i>Better to punch than get punched ♪</i>

16:44.420 --> 16:46.505
<i>♪ Better to burn than get burned ♪</i>

16:46.588 --> 16:50.467
<i>♪ Learn that and you're gonna go far ♪</i>

16:50.551 --> 16:55.097
<i>♪ 'Cause that's the way things are</i>
<i>Ha, na, na, na, na, na, na, na, na ♪</i>

16:55.180 --> 17:00.102
<i>Ha, na, na, na, na, na, na, na ♪</i>

17:00.185 --> 17:01.603
Let's party, people!

17:03.480 --> 17:07.026
<i>-♪ According to Chris ♪</i>
<i>-♪ The world according to Chris ♪</i>

17:07.109 --> 17:09.778
<i>-♪ Her world ♪</i>
<i>-♪ The world according to Chris ♪</i>

17:09.862 --> 17:13.115
<i>-♪ According to Chris ♪</i>
<i>-♪ The world according to Chris ♪</i>

17:13.198 --> 17:16.452
<i>-♪ Her world ♪</i>
<i>-♪ The world according to Chris ♪</i>

17:16.535 --> 17:18.954
<i>♪ Her world ♪</i>

17:29.798 --> 17:32.760
Okay, Veronica,
I am obsessed with everything.

17:32.843 --> 17:36.513
Thank you. It helps to be off-book
and in full costume.

17:38.265 --> 17:39.725
Don't be so modest.

17:40.768 --> 17:43.479
You're the literal embodiment of Chris.

17:43.562 --> 17:46.440
Never has a role been
so perfectly typecast.

17:46.523 --> 17:47.441
Betty.

17:49.651 --> 17:51.445
What was that, Betty?

17:52.571 --> 17:54.114
I mean, think about it.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.076
Spoiled rich girl, check.

17:57.826 --> 18:00.621
Major daddy issues, check.

18:00.704 --> 18:02.081
Bad to the bone,

18:02.164 --> 18:06.585
trying to control everyone,
including her boyfriend and best friend,

18:06.668 --> 18:08.003
check, check, check.

18:11.673 --> 18:14.009
How could you be so mean?
-Archie--

18:14.093 --> 18:17.513
Betty, you have no idea
what's going on with Veronica.

18:18.514 --> 18:22.392
All this intense stuff with her family,
the pressure she's under.

18:22.976 --> 18:24.228
She's trying her best

18:24.311 --> 18:27.231
-under insane circumstances.

18:27.397 --> 18:30.943
Please, help me understand
so I can let this go.

18:31.026 --> 18:32.820
It's not for me to say, Betty.

18:32.903 --> 18:35.656
You remember how quickly she forgave you

18:35.739 --> 18:38.867
when the Black Hood made you say
those horrible things?

18:39.076 --> 18:43.163
So, really, who should be playing Chris
and who should be playing Sue?

18:47.417 --> 18:49.294
Archie, Betty, can you join us?

18:49.378 --> 18:52.214
We're ready to run
Tommy and Sue's love ballad.

19:02.349 --> 19:06.979
<i>♪ </i> <i>If you could see</i>
<i>The way that you look to me ♪</i>

19:07.062 --> 19:11.817
<i>♪ I bet that you'd be amazed</i>
<i>At the sight ♪</i>

19:12.401 --> 19:16.530
<i>♪ You'd see a heart</i>
<i>That's fearless and true ♪</i>

19:17.114 --> 19:20.159
<i>♪ From my point of view ♪</i>

19:20.242 --> 19:24.121
<i>♪ Oh, you shine ♪</i>

19:32.754 --> 19:33.589
V.

19:35.799 --> 19:38.927
Betty, if you're here
to rip into me again,

19:39.011 --> 19:41.847
I agree with what you said back there.

19:42.973 --> 19:46.059
If there's anything
playing Chris has illuminated,

19:46.351 --> 19:49.563
it's that I've been a terrible friend.

19:50.355 --> 19:52.566
I couldn't disagree more.

19:54.401 --> 19:59.489
♪  <i>I think you hide so much</i>
<i>You feel inside ♪</i>

19:59.573 --> 20:04.036
<i>♪ But I know deep down</i>
<i>There's a fire burning bright ♪</i>

20:04.661 --> 20:08.665
<i>♪ From where you stand</i>
<i>It might not be clear ♪</i>

20:09.458 --> 20:12.419
<i>♪ But you shine from here ♪</i>

20:14.171 --> 20:18.550
<i>♪ No doubt</i>
<i>No more fears ♪</i>

20:19.134 --> 20:23.555
<i>♪ I see you shine</i>
<i>And the dark disappears ♪</i> <i>♪ Then I know everything</i>
<i>Is gonna be fine ♪</i>

20:29.519 --> 20:35.984
<i>♪ Because you shine</i>
<i>Just how you shine ♪</i>

20:47.746 --> 20:49.289
Afternoon, gentlemen.

20:50.457 --> 20:54.753
I came to check on the show I'm producing,
and lo and behold, Fred Andrews.

20:57.339 --> 20:59.633
I'm just donating my free time, Hiram.

21:02.386 --> 21:05.806
-Mr. Lodge--

21:05.889 --> 21:09.601
In the new Firebird I bought him?
For the help he's given me.

21:11.687 --> 21:13.897
Yeah, it's a pretty smooth ride.

21:15.983 --> 21:16.900
Yeah.

21:18.819 --> 21:21.363
A young man never forgets his first car.

21:36.670 --> 21:38.046
<i>Dad, it's just a car.</i>

21:38.130 --> 21:42.134
Just a car?
Did I raise you to be that spoiled?

21:44.678 --> 21:46.930
This doesn't have to be a big deal.

21:47.597 --> 21:49.433
It is to me, son.

21:51.018 --> 21:54.438
I was planning on us
picking out an old jalopy.

21:54.521 --> 21:58.400
We could've fixed it up,
like me and Grandpa Artie did.

22:06.950 --> 22:10.746
Honey, I'm sure you're probably
still upset with me,

22:10.829 --> 22:14.499
but I still miss you,
and I am worried about you.

22:18.462 --> 22:19.755
I love you, Chic.

22:21.131 --> 22:23.008
Please call me when you can.

22:27.804 --> 22:29.139
Mom?

22:30.474 --> 22:35.687
Your brother won't return my calls.
Not that I blame him, for what I did.

22:36.730 --> 22:39.232
I'm gonna get water.
Do you want anything?

22:40.233 --> 22:44.529
Jughead, the sandbag was an accident,
and the letter was a prank, right?

22:44.613 --> 22:45.447
Seems like it.

22:45.530 --> 22:48.950
That's what I thought,
but I found this in my locker.

22:49.034 --> 22:50.994
A letter from the Black Hood.

22:51.078 --> 22:53.997
"This is your last warning
to replace Cheryl.

22:54.081 --> 22:56.416
Next time, the sandbag won't miss."

23:03.131 --> 23:07.052
Cheryl, it's your safety.
I have to recast the role of Carrie.

23:07.135 --> 23:09.638
I will not succumb to thespian terrorism and allow myself to be ousted from this.

23:12.599 --> 23:15.268
After the fires
I've walked through, Kevin, the world needs to see me
up on that stage,

23:18.105 --> 23:20.232
a phoenix reborn in the spotlight.

23:20.315 --> 23:23.193
Well, they'll have to wait, Cheryl.

23:24.361 --> 23:27.656
-Mother.
-Even in a town as twisted as Riverdale,

23:27.739 --> 23:32.911
students require parental approval
to partake in extracurricular activities,

23:32.994 --> 23:35.080
As I reminded Principal Weatherbee

23:35.163 --> 23:38.792
when I told him you didn't have
my approval to do the musical,

23:38.875 --> 23:39.918
and never will.

23:40.502 --> 23:43.839
So, you just feast
on broken dreams now, is that it?

23:43.922 --> 23:47.968
Playing a murderous telekinetic teen
who kills her mother?

23:48.635 --> 23:49.845
Please.

23:49.928 --> 23:54.057
This matricidal revenge fantasy,

23:54.975 --> 23:56.601
never gonna happen.

23:57.686 --> 23:58.770
That's final.

24:11.116 --> 24:17.164
Due to some circumstances, Cheryl
will no longer be playing Carrie White.

24:20.625 --> 24:23.420
Penelope Blossom
isn't much of a stage mom.

24:26.590 --> 24:28.425
Cheryl's by the gym bleachers.

24:31.928 --> 24:34.556
Cheryl's understudy will assume the role.

24:34.639 --> 24:36.057
Understudy?

24:36.141 --> 24:38.852
I appointed one
after the sandbag incident.

24:41.563 --> 24:42.439
Midge Klump.

24:48.445 --> 24:50.071
<i> Screw the musical.</i>

24:50.655 --> 24:54.618
I just wanted to prove to everyone
that I'm still me.

24:55.202 --> 24:57.120
But maybe I'm not.

24:58.455 --> 25:03.210
Toni, even Carrie White could stand up
to her mother.

25:03.668 --> 25:07.005
Cheryl, you gotta show your mother
who's in charge.

25:08.548 --> 25:10.425
I don't know if I can anymore.

25:11.426 --> 25:14.721
I'm not the same girl
who burned down Thornhill.

25:14.804 --> 25:15.847
Sure you are.

25:16.640 --> 25:21.228
You're not done playing Carrie, Cheryl,
not by a long shot.

25:30.362 --> 25:35.700
<i>♪ </i> <i>Stay here instead</i>
<i>Just tell me what you'd like to do ♪</i>

25:39.162 --> 25:43.750
<i>♪ We'll talk and we'll laugh</i>
<i>And I'll sing to you ♪</i>

25:43.833 --> 25:46.795
<i>♪ And I promise you, we won't fight ♪</i>

25:47.921 --> 25:50.632
<i>♪ Don't leave tonight ♪</i>

25:53.343 --> 25:56.721
<i>♪ You don't know these people</i>
<i>They're not your friends ♪</i>

25:56.805 --> 25:59.266
<i>♪ Carrie ♪</i>

26:00.433 --> 26:03.520
<i>♪ They're only waiting</i>
<i>To tear you in two ♪</i>

26:04.437 --> 26:06.189
What if they like me?

26:06.439 --> 26:09.693
<i>♪ Just like your father</i>
<i>They'll leave when they're through ♪</i>

26:09.776 --> 26:12.904
-They might like me. They'll like me.
-You're a fool.

26:14.906 --> 26:18.535
<i>♪ </i> <i>Aren't you aware</i>
<i>how people deceive? ♪</i>

26:18.618 --> 26:22.914
<i>♪ They'll take you and break you</i>
<i>And then they will leave you ♪</i>

26:22.998 --> 26:27.627
<i>♪ Carrie</i>
<i>Carrie ♪</i>

26:27.711 --> 26:30.046
<i>♪ Carrie ♪</i>

26:30.130 --> 26:34.259
<i>♪ You are the love I was betrayed for ♪</i>

26:34.342 --> 26:40.307
<i>♪ My pride and my shame</i>
<i>My Betty ♪</i>

26:44.561 --> 26:46.855
<i>♪ We're one and the same ♪</i>

26:51.901 --> 26:53.570
<i>♪ Don't go ♪</i>

26:57.699 --> 26:58.742
Don't go.

27:02.370 --> 27:05.373
<i>♪</i>  <i>Don't go ♪</i>

27:10.378 --> 27:11.421
Mom?

27:17.302 --> 27:22.015
Don't leave me, Betty.
Don't leave me like all the others did.

27:30.065 --> 27:33.526
Am I directing a train wreck?
And where's my tea?

27:40.158 --> 27:41.451
Mom.

27:42.452 --> 27:44.162
I'm not going anywhere, okay?

27:44.245 --> 27:45.997
Everything is crumbling.

27:47.707 --> 27:48.875
I've lost everyone.

27:48.958 --> 27:52.796
No, I haven't lost everyone.
I've driven everyone away.

27:56.299 --> 28:00.595
I gave my son away when he was born.

28:01.638 --> 28:04.057
And then I just did it again.

28:05.517 --> 28:07.727
And your father and I aren't together

28:07.811 --> 28:11.981
because we're still fighting
about something that happened years ago.

28:13.733 --> 28:16.903
And you and I have never been so frayed.

28:31.084 --> 28:33.920
<i>My mom's always been</i>
<i>a woman on the verge.</i>

28:35.130 --> 28:37.674
I have to do something
to help her, Jughead.

28:40.051 --> 28:45.181
Something to make her feel less alone
and abandoned.

28:48.435 --> 28:51.396
Guys, the programs are in,
and they look amazing.

28:51.479 --> 28:54.524
Make sure to get them signed
on opening night.

29:03.992 --> 29:07.245
-Gotta get the sets in.

29:07.328 --> 29:09.456
Yeah. I guess I just assumed--

29:09.539 --> 29:12.333
That I would quit
because we had a disagreement?

29:12.417 --> 29:14.252
That's not the way I roll.

29:19.424 --> 29:22.010
When Kevin came to me about Carrie,

29:22.093 --> 29:24.888
he said I was the embodiment
of Tommy Ross.

29:26.014 --> 29:28.516
Loyal, selfless...

29:29.976 --> 29:32.729
a hero, a force for good.

29:34.898 --> 29:36.733
But I'm none of those things.

29:39.736 --> 29:41.738
I'm not the hero of any story.

29:41.821 --> 29:44.574
<i>Lately I've been going down</i>
<i>this dark path,</i>

29:44.657 --> 29:46.618
<i>ignoring how much it hurt my dad.</i>

29:47.243 --> 29:49.329
<i>I gotta get something off my chest.</i>

29:50.830 --> 29:55.168
You may be my boss, but please,
don't try to get between me and my dad.

29:55.752 --> 29:57.670
Because I promise you, sir...

29:59.297 --> 30:03.760
that is a battle you will lose,
every time.

30:09.599 --> 30:11.476
Thank you for the Firebird...

30:14.687 --> 30:16.815
but I won't be needing it anymore.

30:33.122 --> 30:34.749
Oh, who are we kidding?

30:35.375 --> 30:39.337
It's opening night.
We're too nervous to eat, anyway.

30:46.052 --> 30:46.970
Alice?

30:58.231 --> 30:59.107
Thank you. Welcome.

31:05.321 --> 31:06.823
I'm allergic to peonies.

31:06.906 --> 31:11.077
But how would you know that?
We've only been married for decades.

31:18.459 --> 31:22.046
I'd really like to come back home, Alice.

31:23.631 --> 31:25.466
If you'll have me.

31:35.685 --> 31:40.565
If we do this, Hal, there can't
be any more secrets between us.

31:47.196 --> 31:49.824
-Yeah. There's something you should know
about Chic.

32:06.049 --> 32:10.386
To be honest, I always suspected
that Chic wasn't mine.

32:13.514 --> 32:15.058
I don't care, Alice.

32:16.643 --> 32:18.102
I wanna come home.

32:22.982 --> 32:24.025
Alice.

32:31.199 --> 32:33.743
Our secrets can't hurt us anymore.

32:39.082 --> 32:40.750
We can be together again.

32:57.517 --> 33:01.646
-I do, but this couldn't wait.

33:03.523 --> 33:05.441
I gave back the Firebird, Dad.

33:05.525 --> 33:09.696
Then I sold some of my stuff
so I could buy this off Junkyard Steve.

33:26.337 --> 33:29.841
It needs a lot of work, Dad...
but I'm up for it if you are.

33:37.306 --> 33:41.936
You better get going, Arch.
I don't want you to be late.

33:51.946 --> 33:54.532
<i>♪ </i> <i>You ain't seen nothin' yet ♪</i>

33:55.116 --> 33:58.119
<i>♪ It's gonna be a night</i>
<i>You'll never forget ♪</i>

33:58.202 --> 34:00.288
<i>♪ You ain't seen nothin' yet ♪</i>

34:00.747 --> 34:03.666
<i>♪ It's gonna be a night</i>
<i>We'll never forget ♪</i>

34:04.667 --> 34:06.669
<i>♪ This will be just great ♪</i>

34:06.753 --> 34:09.088
<i>♪ Oh, my life is gonna take flight ♪</i>

34:09.172 --> 34:12.133
<i>♪ Can't wait till Saturday night ♪</i>

34:12.216 --> 34:14.260
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

34:14.343 --> 34:17.346
<i>-♪ Eighty bucks for a tux ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Damn, we better get laid ♪</i>

34:17.430 --> 34:20.933
<i>♪ You've been prayin' for that</i>
<i>Since the seventh grade ♪</i>

34:21.017 --> 34:24.771
<i>♪ It's the least we deserve</i>
<i>After everything we've paid ♪</i>

34:25.813 --> 34:26.647
<i>♪ Got the food ♪</i>

34:26.731 --> 34:27.690
Got the drinks.

34:27.774 --> 34:29.025
<i>♪ Got the limo for ten ♪</i>

34:29.108 --> 34:32.278
<i>♪ And we won't get a chance</i>
<i>Like this again ♪</i>

34:32.361 --> 34:37.075
<i>♪ We'll be leaving as boys</i>
<i>But we're coming home as men ♪</i>

34:37.158 --> 34:39.243
<i>♪ This will be just great ♪</i>

34:39.327 --> 34:44.665
<i>-♪ Yeah, my life is gonna take flight ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Can't wait till Saturday night ♪</i>

34:44.749 --> 34:50.213
<i>♪ You ain't seen nothin' yet</i>
<i>It's gonna be a night we'll never forget ♪</i>

34:50.296 --> 34:56.260
<i>♪ You ain't seen nothin' yet</i>
<i>It's gonna be a night we'll never forget ♪</i>

34:56.344 --> 35:00.973
<i>♪ I believe in getting even</i>
<i>That's what I believe ♪</i>

35:01.057 --> 35:04.852
<i>♪ And I just don't forgive and forget ♪</i>

35:08.940 --> 35:13.861
<i>♪ You ain't seen nothing yet</i>
<i>It's gonna be a night we'll never forget ♪</i>

35:13.945 --> 35:19.492
<i>♪ You ain't seen nothin' yet</i>
